{"type":"message","id":"bcdc7719","parentId":"0f641211","timestamp":"2026-04-10T10:21:48.792Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the results show \"5371.24%\" returns which is impossible - that's clearly a bug. The \"回撤: -1352.61%\" means the max drawdown is -1352%, which means the equity went negative at some point. That's not possible with just 100,000 starting capital.\n\nThe issue is likely in the lambda closure in the loop - the lambda is capturing the loop variable by reference, not by value. So all the lambda functions end up using the last value of the loop variables.\n\nLet me fix this by properly capturing the loop variables in the lambda. I need to use default arguments to capture values.\n\nActually, I see I already did use default arguments in the lambda: `lambda d, rp=rsi_p, o=os, ms=ma_s, ml=ma_l: rsi_ma(d, rp, o, ms, ml)`. \n\nBut the bug is that the lambda function is using the outer scope variables directly in the function call. The `rsi_ma(d, rp=rsi_p, o=os, ms=ma_s, ml=ma_l)` - when the lambda is called later, `rsi_p`, `os`, `ma_s`, `ma_l` will have their values from the loop iteration when the lambda was created, but the way I've written it might still be capturing the loop variable instead of the current value. The closing over the loop variable is still happening because `rsi_p`, `os`, `ms`, and `ml` are being referenced directly in the lambda body rather than being bound as default arguments at definition time.\n\nThe default argument approach should work since default arguments are evaluated once when the function is defined, not when it's called. But looking at the suspicious 5371% return value with a -1352% drawdown, this suggests the strategy is generating massively negative equity somewhere - possibly the RSI values or moving average calculations are being computed incorrectly for certain dates, causing the strategy to take large losing positions. Since the max drawdown is much worse than -100%, the equity curve must be going deeply negative at some point, which means there's a bug in how the strategy is calculating positions or losses.\n\nLooking at the equity dates and values - the equity should always stay positive since we're just doing buy/sell with 100k starting capital and no leverage. But the drawdown being negative by more than 100% suggests the equity went below zero at some point, which shouldn't be possible. This makes me think the bug might be in the lambda capture or in how the backtest function is calculating returns, not necessarily in the strategy logic itself.\n\nThe lambda issue with loop variables is a known Python problem - closures capture variables by reference, not by value. Even though the search function passes default arguments, there might be something else going on. Looking at the 5371% return with -1352% drawdown, that's clearly impossible for a simple long-only strategy, which suggests the bug is likely in how the strategy parameters are being captured or applied during the search.\n\nNow I'm examining the backtest logic itself - specifically how signals are processed. The strategy generates 1 for buy and -1 for sell, and the backtest executes these signals. But there might be a timing issue where the same day can trigger both a buy and sell signal, or the lambda closure in the parameter search is creating duplicate strategy instances with conflicting signals.\n\nThe core problem is likely in how the lambda captures loop variables. When I define a lambda inside a loop with `rp=rsi_p`, `o=os`, `ms=ma_s`, `ml=ma_l` as default arguments, those values should be frozen at definition time, but something's going wrong. I think the real issue is simpler - maybe the lambda isn't actually capturing the values correctly, or there's confusion about which strategy is being evaluated in the results.\n\nActually, wait - if I pass the strategy function directly to backtest without the lambda wrapper, I can verify whether the RSI+MA strategy itself works correctly. Let me test the best parameters from the search directly to see if the results make sense.\n","thinkingSignature":"c1d4b173d950586d824045ca64d0a0b5b2b6a2f2bd842db171130a125ab29842"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n那些收益率数据明显是 bug（回撤-1352%不可能）。是 lambda 闭包捕获的问题。让我直接测试正确参数：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4bd1181970434e74888d0945","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport baostock as bs\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\nlg = bs.login()\nrs = bs.query_history_k_data_plus('sh.000300', 'date,open,high,low,close,volume',\n    start_date='2024-01-01', end_date='2026-04-10', frequency='d')\ndata_list = []\nwhile rs.error_code == '0' and rs.next():\n    data_list.append(rs.get_row_data())\ndf = pd.DataFrame(data_list, columns=rs.fields)\ndf['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])\ndf = df.set_index('date')\nfor col in ['open','high','low','close','volume']:\n    df[col] = pd.to_numeric(df[col], errors='coerce')\ndf = df.dropna()\nbs.logout()\n\nbenchmark = (df.iloc[-1]['close'] / df.iloc[0]['close'] - 1) * 100\nprint(f\"沪深300买入持有: {benchmark:.1f}%\\n\")\n\ndef rsi_ma_strategy(data, rsi_p=7, os=25, ma_s=5, ma_l=20):\n    \"\"\"RSI超卖 + 均线死叉止盈\"\"\"\n    sig = pd.Series(0, index=data.index)\n    delta = data['close'].diff()\n    gain = delta.where(delta > 0, 0).rolling(rsi_p).mean()\n    loss = (-delta.where(delta < 0, 0)).rolling(rsi_p).mean()\n    rsi = 100 - (100 / (1 + gain/(loss+1e-10)))\n    ma_s_ = data['close'].rolling(ma_s).mean()\n    ma_l_ = data['close'].rolling(ma_l).mean()\n    sig[rsi < os] = 1\n    sig[(ma_s_ < ma_l_) & (ma_s_.shift(1) >= ma_l_.shift(1))] = -1\n    return sig\n\ndef backtest(data, strategy_func):\n    capital = 100000.0\n    cash = capital\n    shares = 0\n    trades = []\n    signals = strategy_func(data)\n    \n    equity_dates = []\n    equity_values = []\n    current_cash = cash\n    current_shares = 0\n    \n    for date, row in data.iterrows():\n        price = row['close']\n        equity_dates.append(date)\n        equity_values.append(current_cash + current_shares * price)\n        \n        if date not in signals.index or pd.isna(signals.loc[date]):\n            continue\n        \n        sig = signals.loc[date]\n        \n        if sig == 1 and current_shares == 0 and current_cash > price:\n            n = int(current_cash / price * 0.95)\n            if n > 0:\n                current_cash -= n * price * 1.0003\n                current_shares = n\n                trades.append((date.date(), '买入', price, n))\n        elif sig == -1 and current_shares > 0:\n            current_cash += current_shares * price * 0.9997\n            trades.append((date.date(), '卖出', price))\n            current_shares = 0\n    \n    final_price = data.iloc[-1]['close']\n    final_value = current_cash + current_shares * final_price\n    total_ret = (final_value - capital) / capital\n    annual = (1 + total_ret) ** (252 / len(data)) - 1\n    \n    equity = pd.Series(equity_values, index=equity_dates)\n    returns = equity.pct_change().dropna()\n    sharpe = returns.mean() / returns.std() * np.sqrt(252) if returns.std() > 0 else 0\n    peak = equity.cummax()\n    max_dd = ((equity - peak) / peak).min()\n    \n    buys = [t for t in trades if t[1]=='买入']\n    sells = [t for t in trades if t[1]=='卖出']\n    wins = sum(1 for i,t in enumerate(sells) if i < len(buys) and t[2] > buys[i][2])\n    win = wins / len(sells) if sells else 0\n    \n    return {\n        'total': total_ret, 'annual': annual, 'sharpe': sharpe,\n        'max_dd': max_dd, 'trades': len(trades), 'win': win,\n        'equity': equity, 'trades': trades, 'final_value': final_value\n    }\n\n# 直接测试最优参数\nprint(\"=\" * 65)\nprint(\"🔍 直接测试最优参数\")\nprint(\"=\" * 65)\n\ntest_params = [\n    (7, 25, 8, 25),  # RSI(7,25) MA(8/25)\n    (6, 25, 3, 25),  # RSI(6,25) MA(3/25)\n    (6, 20, 5, 30),  # RSI(6,20) MA(5/30)\n    (7, 25, 5, 20),  # 之前的最优\n    (5, 20, 10, 25),\n    (6, 30, 3, 25),\n]\n\nresults = []\nfor rp, os, ms, ml in test_params:\n    r = backtest(df, lambda d, rp=rp, os=os, ms=ms, ml=ml: rsi_ma_strategy(d, rp, os, ms, ml))\n    results.append((f\"RSI({rp},{os})MA({ms}/{ml})\", r))\n\nresults.sort(key=lambda x: x[1]['total'], reverse=True)\n\nprint(f\"{'策略':<18} {'总收益':>8} {'年化':>8} {'夏普':>6} {'回撤':>8} {'交易':>5} {'vs基准':>8}\")\nprint(\"-\" * 70)\n\nfor name, r in results:\n    diff = r['total']*100 - benchmark\n    mark = \" 🔥\" if diff > 0 else \"\"\n    print(f\"{name:<18} {r['total']*100:>7.2%} {r['annual']*100:>7.2%} {r['sharpe']:>6.3f} {r['max_dd']*100:>7.2%} {r['trades']:>5} {diff:>+7.2%}{mark}\")\n\nprint()\nbest_name, best_r = results[0]\nprint(f\"🏆 最佳: {best_name}\")\nprint(f\"   收益: {best_r['total']*100:.2f}% (vs基准 {best_r['total']*100-benchmark:+.2f}%)\")\nprint(f\"   年化: {best_r['annual']*100:.2f}% | 夏普: {best_r['sharpe']:.3f} | 回撤: {best_r['max_dd']*100:.2f}%\")\n\n# 打印交易记录\nprint()\nprint(\"📋 最近交易:\")\nfor t in best_r['trades'][-10:]:\n    print(f\"   {t[0]} {t[1]} {t[2]:.2f}\" + (f\" x{t[3]}\" if len(t)>3 else \"\"))\nEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":957,"output":2508,"cacheRead":83392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86857,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775816442759,"responseId":"062801fc05db53d9e6565976fec74a8c"}}
