 practical for real coding work with tools like Claude Code.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2effbaa80b5e5397\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.98998636\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5782a817f0ddab50\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOMLX: Anyone working with it yet? : r/LocalLLM\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5782a817f0ddab50\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/LocalLLM/comments/1s08k2q/omlx_anyone_working_with_it_yet/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"064e109567211a8b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# OMLX: Anyone working with it yet? Skip to main contentOMLX: Anyone working with it yet? Open menu Open navigationGo to Reddit Home. Get App Get the Reddit app Log InLog in to Reddit. Expand user menu Open settings menu. # OMLX: Anyone working with it yet? Was reading about it on another sub and thought I’d see if anyone here had experience with it. Supposed to be optimized for Mac and can import the models you already have in LMStudio. Debating installing it and seeing how it works though I just finally got Hermes agent running and am not ready to break things again. Experience with OMLX for Mac users. Comparison of OMLX and Ollama. Best practices for using LMStudio with OMLX. Differences between LMStudio and Ollama. Best practices for training local LLMs. Create your account and connect with a world of communities. Anyone can view, post, and comment to this community. Reddit RulesPrivacy PolicyUser AgreementYour Privacy ChoicesAccessibilityReddit, Inc.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"064e109567211a8b\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9693242\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"oMLX app macOS menu bar 2025","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":2427,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5e2fb0ab34933760\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n